2020 Compared with 2019
The organic sales decrease of $4.1 billion in 2020 compared to 2019 primarily reflects lower commercial aftermarket sales of
$3.8 billion, due to a significant reduction in shop visits and related spare part sales, and lower commercial OEM sales of
$1.1 billion, primarily due to a significant reduction in commercial engine deliveries, all principally driven by the current(1) (2)
