economic and operating environment primarily due to the COVID-19 pandemic. These declines were partially offset by higher
military sales of $0.8 billion primarily driven by an increase in F135 engine sales and aftermarket growth on multiple platforms.
Included in the lower commercial aftermarket sales is a $0.4 billion impact to sales from the net unfavorable contract adjustments
