FAS/CAS operating adjustment
The segment results of RIS and RMD only include pension and PRB expense as determined under U.S. government CAS, which
we generally recover through the pricing of our products and services to the U.S. government. The difference between our CAS
expense and the FAS service cost attributable to these segments under U.S. GAAP is the FAS/CAS operating adjustment. The
FAS/CAS operating adjustment results in consolidated pension expense in operating profit equal to the service cost component of
FAS expense under U.S. GAAP. The segment results of Collins Aerospace and Pratt & Whitney include FAS service cost.
The pension and PRB components of the FAS/CAS operating adjustment were as follows:
(dollars in millions) 2020 2019 2018
