As a result of the Raytheon Merger, Raytheon Company’s contracts accounted for on a percentage of completion basis were reset to
zero percent complete as of the merger date, since only the unperformed portion of the contract at the merger date represents the
obligation of the Company. For additional information related to the Raytheon Merger, see “Note 2: Acquisitions, Dispositions,
Goodwill and Intangible Assets” within Item 8 of this Form 10-K.
Costs incurred for engineering and development of aerospace products under contracts with customers are capitalized as contract
fulfillment costs, to the extent recoverable from the associated contract margin and customer funding, and subsequently amortized
as the OEM products are delivered to the customer. The estimation of contract margin requires management’s judgment. We
regularly assess capitalized contract fulfillment costs for impairment.(1)
